Adam Frank Nilson

November 15,1977 - March 5,2023

I love you & miss you.

Every year on Christmas, after opening presents, we would (led by Adam) go to Roosevelt Park and take over the sledding hill. Yesterday, in honor of my brother, we did just that. It was a moment I’ll never forget. Therapeutic in a way. Honoring Adam by doing something he loved so much, making memories, laughing with family and making the worlds largest snowman. 😜

On behalf of my family and I, I want to thank every person who has prayed and sent condolences. We have felt the strength & peace they have provided. I have been reminded of the power of family, friends and prayer during this season. Thank you. 

1 Thessalonians 4:13 - We grieve with HOPE…knowing we will see him again.

Do not grow weary in doing good, for in DUE season you will reap a harvest of blessing. Galatians 6:9

If you are seeing this, it’s a reminder to “keep going back” and doing what you know is the right thing to do. It may seem foolish to some, you may feel like nothing is changing… be encouraged.. DUE season is coming!! God is working and His timing is perfect.

It’s time to add another SEASON to your calendar 😜
Spring
Summer
Fall
Winter
*DUE*

I believe YOU can LIVE THE DREAM.

I know….its a commonly used cliche, usually to describe a set of achievements… a dream house, dream job , dream family or dream vacation. 

What if I told you that you don’t have to WAIT for those things to happen in your life to live the dream…. but you could live it NOW!

I believe it all starts with a change of PERSPECTIVE. I believe one perspective shift can change your life!

When we see differently, we tend to live, talk, love and walk differently.

What if we stopped focusing on what we lack, and instead focused on what we do have, and the possibilities our life currently offers us? 

What would change if you truly believed that God was in the middle of your troubles, disappointment and heartache and actually working all things out for your good!? 

Imagine if your dream wasn’t a destination you chased , but a mindset you chose?   I spent ALL of 2021 pouring all my heart, soul, passion and creativity into this project. When I was finished, it was 13 chapters that outline how you can harness the power of perspective in every aspect of your life, and as a result experience more of what we ALL want…. more PEACE, JOY and FULFILLMENT.

I believe it will inspire, challenge and encourage you to live the life Gods designed for you to live.

Friends, I want to encourage you today: The key to experiencing peace and seeing it come to pass in your life, these things you’re hoping for, is to stop and it’s to celebrate partial victories along the way. God wants you to enjoy the process. So you’re not completely out of debt…but guess what? You paid off one credit card. You better cut on that worship song and thank God for it. That’s a partial victory. You haven’t received the whole college degree, you haven’t walked on the platform yet, but guess what? You finished one year. Cut everything down, stop, thank God. That’s progress. When you celebrate the partial victories, when you’re grateful for the good. It’s only a matter of time before God takes you to very good. - @NickNilson

The Bible says, when we ask Jesus into our hearts the old things are gone - our mistakes, our past and He makes us new. Can anyone else testify besides Anaya that God is so good and He’s faithful to wash us clean and give us a new start? 2 Corinthians 5:17 says, “Therefore, if anyone is in Christ, the new creation has comes. The old has gone and the new is here.” I’m looking at people who have experienced this new life in Christ, this new beginning. Maybe today you want a new beginning. Maybe you’re here in the room. Maybe you’re watching online or listening by way of Sirius XM. Can I encourage you? The first step like these and 900 others had to do, was simply let go. Let go of past mistakes and receive His grace. It’s His work today that can make you new. So no matter where you are, your experiences, wherever they’ve taken you to, you can experience this in Jesus today. - @NickNilson

Regardless of your position, whether you’re a student or professor, accountant or CEO, stay-at-home mom or lawyer, any measure of influence we are given from God is given for the benefit of others. Your dream, purpose, gifts, talents, and platform are not just for you; they are for others. How are you exercising your power? 

Leadership, influence, and power are about serving and helping others. THIS is where you discover deep significance, fulfillment, and satisfaction.

Of all the things Jesus COULD have done in the moments before His betrayal and trial, He didn’t teach them about preaching eloquently, or how to grow a church in five ways, or give them a three-point lesson on strategic leadership. The One who holds the universe in His hands….removed His robe, took a towel, and washed feet.
 
In other words, He grabbed a towel and SHOWED them how to exercise authority. He was saying, “Live and lead from this position and place. Move into your world from this position of love.” It’s not about titles or status; it’s about your towel. That’s where the REAL power is.

For all those who want to use their INFLUENCE to make a difference…

Pickup your towel today…it’s time to show your world what real authority & leadership looks like. 

It’s time to make some POWER MOVES.

Meet Aaron Ruiz..

Aaron embodies what “Livin the Dream” is all about. Aaron has muscular dystrophy, yet despite his physical limitations, he chooses to serve EVERY week at Lakewood. You can find him positioned out front greeting every visitor with a HUGE smile. Does he always FEEL like smiling? I’d assume not. Yet, every week, every day, he chooses to be grateful for what he is able to do…. and he looks beyond himself to encourage and serve others. There are few people I encounter every week that has more joy than this guy!

Aaron told me today, “My wheelchair doesn’t define me, GOD DOES.”

Aaron inspires me. He doesn’t complain, he doesn’t act like a victim. He trusts God everyday and uses his situation as a platform to point others to Gods goodness. 

He is truly a living example that your external circumstances don’t determine your quality of life, your PERSPECTIVE of your circumstances does.

We love you Aaron!! Keep LIVIN THE DREAM!!!! 🫶🏼💚🤘🏼
